WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-IN

00:11:52.280 --> 00:11:54.120
And then higher secondary came around…

00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:28.600
"If you study well
until the tenth grade,

00:12:28.680 --> 00:12:31.720
"then you have some time
free to yourselves."

00:12:35.120 --> 00:12:39.600
You'd be done with tenth grade,
with twelfth, then undergrad…

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:14.360
He's paying you a compliment,
first say, "thank you" and then…

00:13:14.440 --> 00:13:16.520
"How does a 20-year-old
become an entrepreneur?"

00:13:16.600 --> 00:13:18.080
First, they have to
recognize their good looks.

00:13:59.920 --> 00:14:02.040
We were made to stand according
to our height during the school assembly.

00:17:25.600 --> 00:17:28.520
Toward the end, he's going to say,
"OK, this is my analogy."

00:22:27.720 --> 00:22:29.160
Until I could figure out
what my next move was.

00:23:26.200 --> 00:23:27.760
"I don't need to attend
a high-end college,

00:23:27.840 --> 00:23:30.080
"I'd like to attend a regular college
that has minimal fee."

00:30:26.920 --> 00:30:29.680
I was tall, I had worn my mother's suit…

00:32:04.200 --> 00:32:06.120
It possibly can't get any worse
than that, right?

00:32:16.920 --> 00:32:18.760
You then start showing up confidently.

00:32:47.760 --> 00:32:49.920
There is a long journey
in between those events.

00:35:57.320 --> 00:35:58.960
"Where will she live?
Which of his friends stay there?

00:35:59.040 --> 00:36:00.720
"How will she manage?" Etc., etc.

00:40:35.040 --> 00:40:37.880
You can criticize foreign brands
as much as you want, it's fine.

00:41:44.360 --> 00:41:47.680
So you figured out that
there are no such products in India,

00:41:47.760 --> 00:41:49.000
and you're gonna have to make it yourself.

00:42:03.960 --> 00:42:05.840
We asked them about their whereabouts,
what they were up to,

00:42:05.920 --> 00:42:09.600
"Get this packet for us",
and then that packet gets lost in transit.

00:42:15.080 --> 00:42:17.480
"Why isn't anybody doing anything
about this in India?"

00:42:38.120 --> 00:42:40.400
It might be a possibility
that it just can't happen in India.

00:44:06.200 --> 00:44:08.840
I want to make a shampoo, how do I do it?

00:44:20.840 --> 00:44:23.080
All that information
is very easily made available to you.

00:49:48.560 --> 00:49:51.880
You can have handmade batches in the lab.

00:51:04.600 --> 00:51:06.560
"All right, my child.
Come, we shall see what can be done."

00:51:57.960 --> 00:51:59.600
And nobody even used to write to us
back in the day.

00:53:21.920 --> 00:53:25.000
We were supposed to make five pieces,
and we handmade a batch.

00:55:59.960 --> 00:56:03.160
We found a really premium toy shop
in South Delhi…

00:56:33.680 --> 00:56:35.280
Now, we couldn't gather feedback
from kids,

00:56:35.360 --> 00:56:36.880
we obviously had to make the pitch
to their parents.

00:58:16.120 --> 00:58:18.080
"How will we make 20 products?"

00:58:41.000 --> 00:58:42.840
We used to call this
"bulk orders" back then.

01:00:29.760 --> 01:00:31.360
Who is going to explain that
to the consumer?

01:01:19.160 --> 01:01:21.320
Anyone can go ahead
and replicate your product.

01:04:10.160 --> 01:04:11.560
"What are you giving for free?"

01:06:36.280 --> 01:06:39.200
…nobody in the Indian beauty and personal
care industry had done any innovation.

01:06:43.480 --> 01:06:46.040
"The English came, and they brought
with them their thick creams.

01:06:46.120 --> 01:06:48.320
"The English might have left,
but they left their creams behind."

01:12:09.680 --> 01:12:10.760
It's your autobiography.

01:15:01.400 --> 01:15:03.640
"A biodata was created
around the time of my marriage.

01:15:03.720 --> 01:15:05.320
"I haven't created any bio after that."

01:15:07.880 --> 01:15:10.960
No, your bio was formed,
it's just that you didn't create one.

01:15:50.160 --> 01:15:51.520
Separation is always sad.

01:16:01.680 --> 01:16:06.960
No, but I think it's common in India,
around 95-98%.

01:16:07.040 --> 01:16:09.360
This is, like, bound to happen.

01:20:29.760 --> 01:20:35.760
From his office, steal some fabric,
and go to the tailor, get it stitched.

01:20:35.840 --> 01:20:38.200
Sit there and instruct him.
"Cut it like this, like that."

01:21:00.480 --> 01:21:02.760
There's a lot of hard work in that too.

01:21:02.840 --> 01:21:07.000
To plan, make chits, mapping it all.

01:21:07.080 --> 01:21:08.480
I said, "Forget all this."

01:21:27.000 --> 01:21:29.240
A businessman carries
a suitcase to the office.

01:21:29.320 --> 01:21:33.600
In 5th standard, I carried a VIP suitcase
for the first time.

01:21:37.520 --> 01:21:38.560
Yes.

01:21:47.760 --> 01:21:49.360
I have never seen cash before.

01:22:18.640 --> 01:22:19.760
The cloth used to cost 1 rupee.

01:23:09.000 --> 01:23:12.000
Selling the 1 rupee material
for 1.25 rupees. That was the best.

01:23:33.120 --> 01:23:34.320
Or how to enter.

01:24:09.240 --> 01:24:11.320
The boss can go anywhere.

01:24:40.200 --> 01:24:42.080
He said he wanted that trade.

01:24:44.640 --> 01:24:47.360
Give it to me for one rupee,
I want this deal in my name.

01:25:07.920 --> 01:25:11.320
How old is your company?
He said, "It hasn't been established yet."

01:25:32.960 --> 01:25:35.800
Fine, please provide a name
to be written in the contract, at least.

01:26:06.320 --> 01:26:09.120
The fabric won't be clean,
it won't be of good quality.

01:26:09.200 --> 01:26:11.840
And I have to sell X quantity.

01:26:13.160 --> 01:26:16.480
So, make 4,000 of these,
or make it in four different locations

01:26:16.560 --> 01:26:19.680
because if I get small amounts
from everywhere, my contract is closed.

01:26:44.160 --> 01:26:46.320
It is very important to be
an exporter these days.

01:26:50.640 --> 01:26:54.520
The dollar was around 25-26 rupees.
I took my bag and left.

01:26:55.680 --> 01:26:59.160
It was the first time that had I ever
seen a dollar, so I left at once.

01:26:59.240 --> 01:27:04.400
Travelled 25 kilometres
on a pedal rickshaw to reach the hotel.

01:27:05.360 --> 01:27:08.080
There was a board
above the rickshaw stand,

01:27:08.160 --> 01:27:10.520
it read "Muhammad E Group",
and I went right in.

01:27:23.560 --> 01:27:26.440
They showed some samples
and took the first order.

01:27:39.120 --> 01:27:41.120
Sushil Sen is there.

01:28:32.880 --> 01:28:35.400
Upon hearing about arts, it felt like…

01:30:34.360 --> 01:30:38.920
I'll pay back my father. If he has spent
4 crores, then I will pay it back.

01:30:39.000 --> 01:30:41.040
-The debt will be cleared.
-You've returned the amount.

01:30:41.120 --> 01:30:43.240
Yes, I mean, what I have done.
I said, "Look…"

01:31:05.160 --> 01:31:06.760
This was not a loan.

01:31:38.280 --> 01:31:39.960
You have to learn
the Snake and Ladder game.

01:35:15.520 --> 01:35:17.200
But, yeah, my sister's wedding
was to be arranged.

01:35:17.280 --> 01:35:19.760
Marwari's stress a lot about that.
Two to three crores are required for that.

01:35:25.240 --> 01:35:27.840
You realize that there's only one left.
Three belong to the daughter.

01:35:27.920 --> 01:35:29.080
There's only one left.

01:39:11.280 --> 01:39:13.040
So, I thought,
it would be a brand from Spain.

01:39:13.920 --> 01:39:19.680
I came home and opened the Apple…
the desktop.

01:40:20.760 --> 01:40:23.640
It's a 1,600 square feet house.
It has been like that from the start.

01:43:13.240 --> 01:43:14.400
If there's no PnL,
there will be no income.

01:43:15.520 --> 01:43:21.520
And I didn't know anything about
the gestation period or valuation.

01:44:42.000 --> 01:44:45.440
I thought, why spend money at a hotel,
I'll just sleep here.

01:45:15.920 --> 01:45:17.720
"You attended the school, right?"
I said, "Yes, I did."

01:45:21.560 --> 01:45:22.640
I said, "Yes, I went there."

01:45:22.720 --> 01:45:25.040
He said, "Do you pay the school fees?"
I said, "Yes."

01:45:25.120 --> 01:45:26.840
The fee for the business
is to claim.

01:45:26.920 --> 01:45:27.960
That's how you'll learn.

01:45:28.040 --> 01:45:29.400
Your father is not going to teach you.

01:45:29.480 --> 01:45:32.040
You took the order, you placed it,
and opened an office.

01:45:32.120 --> 01:45:34.040
And you don't want to see it.
You have your eyes closed.

01:45:34.120 --> 01:45:37.400
You go there and see that
the light is not proper,

01:45:37.480 --> 01:45:40.720
I am sure you were frustrated
and must have sent some messages as well.

01:45:46.280 --> 01:45:47.840
He isn't going to be satisfied anyway.

01:45:54.120 --> 01:45:55.280
That is the journey of WhatsApp.

01:46:11.240 --> 01:46:12.720
And I was the one who had to go abroad.

01:46:31.480 --> 01:46:35.800
But Mom used to beat me
if I scored low marks.

01:46:35.880 --> 01:46:37.600
We were very scared of Mom.

01:46:37.680 --> 01:46:40.840
We were so scared of her
that we would greet her from far away.

01:46:46.000 --> 01:46:47.840
How can you be so innocent?

01:46:48.880 --> 01:46:51.680
How is your saree whiter than my saree?

01:46:51.760 --> 01:46:52.920
We should talk about that.

01:47:31.560 --> 01:47:34.000
If we ask a banker,
he will not say that it is fine,

01:47:34.080 --> 01:47:35.520
in today's immaturity.

01:47:35.600 --> 01:47:39.960
And if we look elsewhere,
we were busy with friends.

01:47:40.040 --> 01:47:41.280
So we didn't know whom to ask.

01:48:05.760 --> 01:48:08.520
I asked someone
what "touching feet" means.

01:48:08.600 --> 01:48:10.960
He said it means you don't have an ego.

01:48:11.720 --> 01:48:13.560
He isn't giving you anything
from the ground underneath.

01:48:15.480 --> 01:48:17.440
And if they place their hand on you,
that doesn't mean anything.

01:48:39.960 --> 01:48:43.640
There was a ladies' shop
behind the Hind Mata theater.

01:48:59.400 --> 01:49:00.560
That place was scary.

01:50:10.240 --> 01:50:12.680
Why would you create a wall in your office
saying that you are busy?

01:50:12.760 --> 01:50:13.920
Nobody is busy.

01:50:16.160 --> 01:50:18.640
You are getting the design, then why?

01:50:32.640 --> 01:50:35.040
They said, "I received your number
from someone."

01:50:35.120 --> 01:50:37.640
I said, "I'll send you a number,
please come."

01:57:25.720 --> 01:57:26.840
It will keep happening.

01:57:26.920 --> 01:57:29.320
There will be one person in the office,
always roaming around.

01:57:29.400 --> 01:57:31.120
The staircase has to be white entirely.

02:00:14.880 --> 02:00:16.640
It was the era of the East India Company.

02:00:27.280 --> 02:00:30.600
It was a Chinese wallet
on which "Jack &amp; Jones" was written.

02:00:30.680 --> 02:00:31.920
So, he said, "Write this."

02:00:34.960 --> 02:00:37.240
Why was there "Jack &amp; Jones"
on a Chinese wallet?

02:01:05.120 --> 02:01:06.320
Our time will also come.

02:04:00.120 --> 02:04:03.880
The depreciation we're getting at the end,
is coming back in the form of taxes.

02:04:03.960 --> 02:04:06.360
I thought this depreciation…

02:04:07.600 --> 02:04:09.120
was some sort of chaos entering our home.

02:04:09.200 --> 02:04:11.640
I did not realize that it was our money
circulating and coming back.

02:04:28.280 --> 02:04:32.920
You are already earning profit.
You are earning 10-15 crores.

02:04:33.000 --> 02:04:35.040
You have to pay this much interest.

02:04:46.320 --> 02:04:51.000
So, you will get this, and in the end
when you get a profit of Rs.10,

02:04:51.680 --> 02:04:56.480
you will get 100 from depreciation,
12%, then the building, etc.

02:04:57.560 --> 02:04:59.920
This gets deducted and in the end,
you've only paid this much tax.

02:06:38.320 --> 02:06:39.600
I said that's what I want to make.

02:06:39.680 --> 02:06:41.320
A factory is not made like this, but…

02:07:19.240 --> 02:07:21.560
I don't care
about your technical problems.

02:08:15.360 --> 02:08:17.480
We have to make it and it would require
explaining it to another person,

02:08:17.560 --> 02:08:18.600
the drawing, etc.

02:09:09.040 --> 02:09:11.480
I said this guy must be big,
don't know for whom.

02:09:11.560 --> 02:09:13.760
Even for you guys,
I had to quickly see,

02:09:13.840 --> 02:09:17.280
have some shame and read about the people
you are meeting.

02:10:06.760 --> 02:10:09.520
No, this was when I had started,
when I was 19 or 20.

02:10:09.600 --> 02:10:13.400
I'd go to clubs, smoking was my problem,
not the drinking.

02:10:13.480 --> 02:10:15.960
I'd hop onto a train,
head straight to the next country,

02:10:16.040 --> 02:10:17.680
so that I could save money on hotels.

02:11:32.640 --> 02:11:34.440
If her son asks her for something to eat
at 12:00 in the night…

02:12:32.280 --> 02:12:34.000
"As if you take great care of me."

02:13:27.200 --> 02:13:28.920
I'm not patient enough
to wait out the gestation period…

02:13:29.000 --> 02:13:30.960
It would make me even more restless.
"How long must I wait?

02:13:31.040 --> 02:13:32.920
"I've been waiting for three years,
six years,

02:13:33.000 --> 02:13:34.920
"hoping that the bulb comes on,
when will it come on?

02:13:35.000 --> 02:13:36.160
"Where is the switch?"

02:15:28.560 --> 02:15:30.000
That is exactly what I'm doing.

02:16:44.640 --> 02:16:47.160
I mean, you looked at him
with such disdain!

02:20:15.040 --> 02:20:17.160
"How I stole cigarettes,
or how I borrowed it from someone,

02:20:17.240 --> 02:20:19.120
"how we managed to go
on our bike, all that…"

02:20:19.200 --> 02:20:20.960
"I don't have enough money to burn."

02:21:06.400 --> 02:21:09.480
…make a balcony, make it out of sandstone.
Do whatever you need to do.

02:23:54.240 --> 02:23:56.720
He must have gotten
his entire house painted for that much.

02:23:57.640 --> 02:23:59.120
He must have sent about 100 pieces;

02:23:59.200 --> 02:24:02.360
he could paint both the exterior
and the interior of your house.

02:24:02.440 --> 02:24:04.720
It is an embroidery order
from Armani, after all.

02:25:19.720 --> 02:25:21.520
…"we aren't getting enough footfall."

02:25:21.600 --> 02:25:22.920
The person on the 21st floor will say,

02:25:23.000 --> 02:25:25.600
"What are you doing, sir?
Nobody even visits our floor."

02:26:06.680 --> 02:26:08.320
You don't know if you're gonna
open the store or not,

02:26:08.400 --> 02:26:10.160
if you can design it or not,
if you have an architect or not,

02:26:10.240 --> 02:26:12.560
will it get constructed or not,
if the goods will arrive or not.

02:26:12.640 --> 02:26:15.280
If it arrives and gets sold out, then when
will the second round of material come?

02:26:15.360 --> 02:26:16.920
You're not gonna say,
"Pull down the shutter,

02:26:17.000 --> 02:26:20.440
"we'll go buy new yarn, make clothes,
bring it back, return after a month."

02:26:20.520 --> 02:26:21.960
Maybe your father has that kind of money.

02:27:21.240 --> 02:27:24.240
The Gandhi&lt;i&gt; ji &lt;/i&gt;khadi,
the kind you get at Udyog Bhawan.

02:28:29.760 --> 02:28:31.160
T-shirts can't be made out of khadi.

02:28:31.240 --> 02:28:32.880
-It can't be made?
-It can't be made? Why?

02:32:28.240 --> 02:32:29.520
"A person from Ludhiana said,

02:32:29.600 --> 02:32:32.760
'Sir, the blingy red shirts
are in vogue these days.'"

02:32:32.840 --> 02:32:35.440
"Someone else says,
'Send us more chequered shirts.'"

02:32:35.520 --> 02:32:39.640
"Some other person says, 'Sir,
increase the length of the sleeves.'"

02:32:39.720 --> 02:32:41.480
You're going to receive
so many comments in this country,

02:32:41.560 --> 02:32:44.480
that your brand will become something else
entirely if you try and handle it.

02:47:34.520 --> 02:47:37.480
"The judge will now hear your arguments."

02:47:37.560 --> 02:47:39.320
This is the right time.

02:49:29.720 --> 02:49:32.480
When a person deboards a train,

02:49:32.560 --> 02:49:37.080
you get to know that this new person
is an alien who's an alien national.

02:49:37.160 --> 02:49:38.560
Not alien in the sense of an "alien."

02:49:38.640 --> 02:49:41.600
You find it in US Immigration forms, yeah,
"Are you an alien?"

02:54:29.160 --> 02:54:30.960
I mean, fine, it's one thing
to educate your kids.

02:54:31.040 --> 02:54:32.880
It's basic amongst the Marwaris
and the Agarwals.

02:54:32.960 --> 02:54:34.400
Education is a basic criteria for them.

03:00:33.920 --> 03:00:36.360
Planes hadn't even flown over
where we used to reside.

03:00:36.440 --> 03:00:38.520
We didn't even know
what it is that a pilot does.

03:00:38.600 --> 03:00:40.240
But it is something
that the elder sister says,

03:00:40.320 --> 03:00:42.800
and she happens to be the smartest
in the family.

03:00:42.880 --> 03:00:44.880
And if she's saying it, then we will
also aspire to become the same.

03:00:44.960 --> 03:00:47.120
There's no confusion about it.

03:00:47.200 --> 03:00:49.600
And after that she said "entrepreneur"…

03:02:52.040 --> 03:02:53.960
A lot of beatings, scolding…

03:03:08.080 --> 03:03:09.440
-A darling.
-Yes.

03:03:09.520 --> 03:03:11.520
I thought that I must
take full advantage of it.

03:07:06.320 --> 03:07:09.000
Often times, people tend to
exaggerate about themselves.

03:07:09.080 --> 03:07:11.080
Why is that? Because they feel that
if they say something wrong,

03:07:11.160 --> 03:07:12.680
you know, what will it mean?

03:13:18.120 --> 03:13:20.560
"Has the money arrived?
Have you deposited it in the account?

03:13:20.640 --> 03:13:23.240
"Is everything all right?"

03:17:10.480 --> 03:17:13.160
"This is where my&lt;i&gt; barsati &lt;/i&gt;is,

03:17:13.240 --> 03:17:16.040
"get off at this metro station
and come over here in an auto."

03:17:16.120 --> 03:17:17.400
"This is where my&lt;i&gt; barsati &lt;/i&gt;is"?

03:17:36.040 --> 03:17:38.880
He said, "I'll have to come by auto,
you don't have a car?"

03:18:18.000 --> 03:18:19.360
"What am I going to get
by being bothered by it?"

03:18:19.440 --> 03:18:20.840
'You're not gonna get more money
in your pocket."

03:18:20.920 --> 03:18:23.200
Like you were saying earlier,
"What can be worse?"

03:18:23.280 --> 03:18:25.320
So, what you have…
You can't deny your reality…

03:18:25.400 --> 03:18:28.040
How many out of the ten managed to make it
all the way to your&lt;i&gt; barsati&lt;/i&gt;?

03:18:28.120 --> 03:18:31.360
The entire entrepreneur crowd made it.

03:18:31.440 --> 03:18:34.560
After that, I went about doing,
how do I put it…

03:18:35.920 --> 03:18:40.880
if there is a problem with your vehicle,
take a different path.

03:18:41.640 --> 03:18:44.320
So I chose a path
which allowed me to meet more people.

03:18:44.400 --> 03:18:45.800
And they happened to be entrepreneurs.

03:18:48.640 --> 03:18:49.920
And I befriended all of them.

03:21:48.960 --> 03:21:52.800
Humility doesn't mean that you only say,
"No, I don't know anything."

03:21:52.880 --> 03:21:54.760
You come across as underconfident.

03:21:54.840 --> 03:21:57.200
According to me,
you should have confidence.

03:22:04.560 --> 03:22:06.600
There definitely has to be something
that one doesn't understand.

03:22:30.600 --> 03:22:33.240
All of my hometown, Raigarh,
would have gotten ladoos

03:22:33.320 --> 03:22:37.840
if I had gotten into Infosys
as an "assistant technical engineer."

03:22:56.320 --> 03:23:00.200
I genuinely feel that something
fortuitous happened

03:23:00.280 --> 03:23:01.840
that led me on my entrepreneurial journey.

03:23:26.920 --> 03:23:30.840
At that time, it was 71 rupees
to a dollar which meant 71 lakhs.

03:23:36.000 --> 03:23:37.880
I was a Rebel Without a Cause…

03:23:37.960 --> 03:23:40.040
And so I hadn't watched
a single movie throughout the year,

03:23:40.120 --> 03:23:43.440
but when I did save some money
from my internship stipend,

03:23:43.520 --> 03:23:45.560
we went to watch a movie
called&lt;i&gt; The Social Network&lt;/i&gt;.

03:23:46.600 --> 03:23:48.400
In that there is a person
named Peter Thiel

03:23:48.480 --> 03:23:50.320
who gives the first $100,000 cheque.

03:30:02.280 --> 03:30:04.160
I was just overjoyed by the fact
that I am going to the USA.

03:30:04.240 --> 03:30:05.760
I was under the impression
that my life is made.

03:30:26.520 --> 03:30:29.000
I was told that I needed
to get my biometrics done,

03:30:29.080 --> 03:30:32.840
provide them with a letter,
and you get your visa.

03:32:36.800 --> 03:32:39.000
…this was a once in a lifetime opportunity
to go the US,

03:32:39.080 --> 03:32:40.720
because not much else
was happening in my life.

03:32:41.480 --> 03:32:43.320
And I was really eager to learn.

03:32:53.680 --> 03:32:55.840
"I want to pay you a visit
and see your office."

03:35:14.560 --> 03:35:16.920
Sahil says,
"I am not aware of who the chairman is,

03:35:17.000 --> 03:35:20.480
"but there is a Ritesh seated next to me,
maybe he can help you."

03:35:28.600 --> 03:35:32.240
"If someone is addressing me
as the chairman, let them."

03:35:32.320 --> 03:35:35.320
I mean, it feels nice to think that
we can also be a chairman.

03:35:35.400 --> 03:35:36.840
You'd already become one.

03:36:13.760 --> 03:36:15.320
"Let us meet once at the very least."

03:36:25.160 --> 03:36:26.200
"It was lovely meeting you."

03:36:50.280 --> 03:36:52.280
"No problem whatsoever.
He's willing to not draw any salary.

03:36:52.360 --> 03:36:54.560
"Such a highly-educated person
is coming to work with us."

03:40:33.600 --> 03:40:35.680
…like, "OYO hasn't even launched…"

03:45:06.840 --> 03:45:09.560
No, no, with cheating. You can pass
school examinations by cheating.

03:45:09.640 --> 03:45:12.720
Nobody even pursues the dream
of becoming an IPS officer.

03:45:12.800 --> 03:45:14.440
IPS is such a far-fetched dream,

03:45:14.520 --> 03:45:16.760
they don't even apply
for the position of a bank PO.

03:45:16.840 --> 03:45:18.800
So if you become an IPS officer
in spite of hailing from Chambal…

03:45:18.880 --> 03:45:20.400
There is a stigma
of being a native of Chambal.

03:45:32.240 --> 03:45:38.720
A European spirit has come
and taken residence within your soul.

03:48:29.400 --> 03:48:32.560
We had already become a chain
of around 15,000 hotels.

03:49:36.120 --> 03:49:41.840
Since you are an Agarwal, a Marwari,
it's a burden for a 20-year-old guy.

03:50:03.240 --> 03:50:05.240
Therefore not raising capital
was not a choice.

03:50:08.360 --> 03:50:11.000
So raising that initial bit of capital
was absolutely necessary.

03:50:16.000 --> 03:50:18.120
The global expansion after it…

03:51:39.960 --> 03:51:41.560
The other person will always think,

03:51:41.640 --> 03:51:44.760
"Okay, they made this mistake
but they are still saying

03:51:44.840 --> 03:51:47.480
"that they will bounce back."
How will that happen?

03:51:56.120 --> 03:52:00.760
There isn't a lot of difference between
action and words in our line of business.

03:54:14.920 --> 03:54:17.520
Be it e-commerce, gaming…
Take any industry, for example…

03:54:36.760 --> 03:54:39.640
"Look, we don't know
what is gonna happen to OYO's stock.

03:54:39.720 --> 03:54:41.840
"We don't know
what is gonna happen to the company."

03:54:44.360 --> 03:54:46.200
…and we were going through a pay cut.

03:55:27.040 --> 03:55:29.400
We don't want to be a company
that has 200-300% growth.

03:55:46.800 --> 03:55:48.960
As long as these three stats are healthy…

03:55:49.040 --> 03:55:50.280
If that doesn't happen, we will not grow.

03:57:01.800 --> 03:57:04.120
But I can read everything
and I am comfortable

03:57:04.200 --> 03:57:06.000
being able to distinguish
between the noise and the signals.

